&lt;p&gt;   **&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Idcmp&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=idcmp)**&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=idcmp)**&lt;/a&gt; opened **&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-149&quot; title=&quot;supressionsFileExpression does not work.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MCHECKSTYLE-149&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MCHECKSTYLE-149&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-149?redirect=false)**&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-149?redirect=false)**&lt;/a&gt; and commented&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   In DefaultCheckstyleExecutor.getOverridingProperties() there is the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   ```java&lt;br/&gt;
     if ( request.getSuppressionsFileExpression() != null )&lt;br/&gt;
           {&lt;br/&gt;
               String suppresionFile = request.getSuppressionsFileExpression();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;               if ( suppresionFile != null )&lt;/p&gt;
               {
                   p.setProperty( request.getSuppressionsFileExpression(), suppresionFile );
               }
&lt;p&gt;           }&lt;br/&gt;
   ```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   Note how supressionFile is being set to the *&lt;b&gt;expression&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;, not the **file&lt;/b&gt;*.  This one line should read:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   ```java&lt;br/&gt;
   String suppresionFile = request.getSuppressionsLocation();&lt;br/&gt;
   ```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   This bug is blocking the m2e-checkstyle plugin from supporting Maven-driven suppression files.&lt;/p&gt;


